2 HOUSE BILL 1499
1 (b) (1) In addition to the clauses required under subsection (a) of this section,
2 a procurement contract for construction shall include:
3 [(1)] (I) a clause providing for contract modification if the condition of a
4 site differs from the condition described in the specifications; [and]
5 [(2)] (II) a clause covering the requirements for notice of contract claims,
6 submission of contract claims, and resolution of contract claims under § 15–219 of this
7 article; AND
8 (III) IF THE CONTRACT IS FOR 3 YEARS OR MORE IN DURATION
9 AND IS VALUED AT GREATER THAN $1,000,000, A CLAUSE REQUIRING CONTRACT
10 MODIFICATION FOR THE EQUITABLE ADJUSTMENT OF THE CONTRACT FOR
11 INCREASED COSTS FOR COMPENSATION AND BENEFITS AS A RESULT OF:
12 1. STATUTORY CHANGES INCREASING REQUIRED
13 COMPENSATION OR BENEFITS; OR
14 2. COLLECTIVE BARGAINING.
15 (2) IN ADDITION TO THE CLAUSES REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (A)
16 OF THIS SECTION, A PROCUREMENT CONTRACT FOR SECURITY SERVICES THAT IS
17 FOR 3 YEARS OR MORE IN DURATION AND IS VALUED AT GREATER THAN $1,000,000
18 SHALL INCLUDE A CLAUSE REQUIRING CONTRACT MODIFICATION FOR THE
19 EQUITABLE ADJUSTMENT OF THE CONTRACT FOR INCREASED COSTS FOR
20 COMPENSATION AND BENEFITS AS A RESULT OF:
21 (I) STATUTORY CHANGES INCREASING REQUIRED
22 COMPENSATION OR BENEFITS; OR
23 (II) COLLECTIVE BARGAINING.
24 (3) A CONTRACT THAT IS MODIFIED IN ACCORDANCE WITH
25 PARAGRAPH (1)(III) OR (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION IS CONTINGENT ON APPROVAL BY
26 THE BOARD.
27 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
28 October 1, 2025 2026.

